## Why Quarkus for APIs?

Quarkus is a Kubernetes-native Java framework tailored for GraalVM and HotSpot. It offers blazing fast startup times (under 0.1s) and low RSS memory, making it ideal for microservices and serverless architectures.

## Key Performance Features

- **Fast Boot Time**: Sub-second startup makes it perfect for containerized environments
- **Low Memory Footprint**: Typically 1/10th of traditional Java frameworks
- **Native Compilation**: Compile to a native binary with GraalVM for even faster startup
- **Reactive Core**: Built on Vert.x for non-blocking I/O

## REST API Example

```java
@Path("/articles")
@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)
public class ArticleResource {

    @Inject
    ContentManagerService contentManager;

    @GET
    public Response listArticles(@QueryParam("page") @DefaultValue("0") int page) {
        List<CmsEntry> entries = contentManager.listEntries(
            "api::article.article", null, "en", page, 20);
        return Response.ok(entries).build();
    }
}
```

## GraphQL Support

The CMS also includes a full GraphQL API with auto-generated schemas, making it easy to query exactly the data you need.
